headline: UnitedHealth, Humana, CVS drop on expanded Medicare Advantage audits
summary: Investing.com -- Shares of major health insurers UnitedHealth (NYSE:UNH), Humana (NYSE:HUM), and CVS (NYSE:CVS) fell sharply today, with UnitedHealth down 4%, Humana declining 5%, and CVS dropping 4% in afterhours trading. The slide came in response to the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services (CMS) announcing a significant expansion of its auditing efforts for Medicare Advantage (MA) plans.
